item.title: Help!
item.dc:creator: @delicious delicious
item.description:
@delicious wrote:

You will need to download AND install Jdk. Probably, you would want this one: http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/widget/jdk6.jsp

Then in your “compiler” if you have one, you will need to look for “jdk1.0.6_17” and will have to change the 17 to an 18.

“jdk1.0.6_18”

Read full topic

item.title: Help!
item.dc:creator: @nardoscape nardoscape
item.description:
@nardoscape wrote:

if your running a server you must have jdk, go to c:/ program files / Java / then youll find your jdk folder.

if your serer is up and running. then go to Compile, right click and hit edit. it should say something like C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.6.0_17\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d …/build/ ./net/com/espeon/.java where Jdk.._** is (* = numbers) enter the jdk you found in your java folder. there you go. Hopefully it works.
